The paper deals with a new camera design that uses compressive sensing for image acquisition and reconstruction. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) as well as information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the use of real-time stitching algorithms, which could fall under numerical analysis (cs.NA) or systems and control (cs.SI).
